text: Ad Graaumans (16 October 1946 â€” 12 November 2016) was a Dutch football midfielder. He played for NAC Breda, PSV and FC Den Bosch. He made his debut for NAC at the age of 16. He played a total of 95 matches for NAC, including the 1967 KNVB Cup final against Ajax Amsterdam. In March 1965 he broke his leg in the match against PSV. In June 1967 he moved to PSV.
